<TITLE> BNP names MK Anwar to recession taskforce </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 19 (bdnews24.com)  Main opposition party BNP has nominated MK Anwar MP to the just-formed recession task force on countering the impact the global recession. The first meeting of the task force is to take place on March 24, the finance minister has said. BNP joint secretary Nazrul Islam Khan told reporters of the party's choice Thursday. Speaking at the party chairperson's Gulshan office, Khan, however, alleged the government was using parliament and the Anticorruption Commission for political gain. "The government has put the image of parliament and the Commission at stake by forming a parliamentary probe committee against former speaker Jamiruddin Sircar and by filing an ACC graft case against Khaleda's younger son Coco ahead of upcoming bi-elections," he said. He said ACC's case against Coco was purely motivated. Raising questions about the decision to probe Sircar's tenure as speaker for graft, he said that this question would not have arisen after the by-election. He attempts were on to affect the by-election results and said "democracy would be on the wane if this happens". BNP office secretary Rizvi Ahmed, chairperson's press secretary Maruf Kamal Khan Sohel, the of the and Habibun Nabi Khan Sohel, former student leader, were present at the briefing among others. bdn
